                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          The actual result of parsing the method depends on the persistence store for which you create the query. However, there are some general things to notice.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="ulist" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em 1.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; list-style-position: outside; font-family: inherit;">
                          <li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.625em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                              The expressions are usually property traversals combined with operators that can be concatenated. You can combine property expressions with&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">AND</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">OR</code>. You also get support for operators such as&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Between</code>,&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">LessThan</code>,<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">GreaterThan</code>,&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Like</code>&nbsp;for the property expressions. The supported operators can vary by datastore, so consult the appropriate part of your reference documentation.</p>
                          </li>
                          <li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.625em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                              The method parser supports setting an&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">IgnoreCase</code>&nbsp;flag for individual properties (for example,<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">findByLastnameIgnoreCase(…)</code>) or for all properties of a type that support ignoring case (usually&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">String</code>&nbsp;instances, for example,&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">findByLastnameAndFirstnameAllIgnoreCase(…)</code>). Whether ignoring cases is supported may vary by store, so consult the relevant sections in the reference documentation for the store-specific query method.</p>
                          </li>
                          <li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.625em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                              You can apply static ordering by appending an&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">OrderBy</code>&nbsp;clause to the query method that references a property and by providing a sorting direction (<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Asc</code>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Desc</code>). To create a query method that supports dynamic sorting, see&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.spring.io/spring-data/jpa/docs/2.0.0.M3/reference/html/#repositories.special-parameters" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); line-height: inherit; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">Special parameter handling</a>.</p>
                          </li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="sect3" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                      <h4 id="repositories.query-methods.query-property-expressions" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 300; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.4375em; word-spacing: -0.05em;">
                        4.4.3. Property expressions (메서드 명 속의 목적어로 프로퍼티명을 그대로 사용해주고 파라미터를 선언하면, 해당 패턴으로 쿼리가 생성된다)</h4>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          Property expressions can refer only to a direct property of the managed entity, as shown in the preceding example. At query creation time you already make sure that the parsed property is a property of the managed domain class. However, you can also define constraints by traversing nested properties. Assume a&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Person</code>&nbsp;has an&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Address</code>&nbsp;with a&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">ZipCode</code>. In that case a method name of</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
                          <pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">List</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Person</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findByAddressZipCode</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">ZipCode</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> zipCode</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span></code></pre>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          creates the property traversal&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">x.address.zipCode</code>. The resolution algorithm starts with interpreting the entire part (<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">AddressZipCode</code>) as the property and checks the domain class for a property with that name (uncapitalized). If the algorithm succeeds it uses that property. If not, the algorithm splits up the source at the camel case parts from the right side into a head and a tail and tries to find the corresponding property, in our example,&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">AddressZip</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Code</code>. If the algorithm finds a property with that head it takes the tail and continue building the tree down from there, splitting the tail up in the way just described. If the first split does not match, the algorithm move the split point to the left (<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Address</code>,<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">ZipCode</code>) and continues.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          Although this should work for most cases, it is possible for the algorithm to select the wrong property. Suppose the<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Person</code>&nbsp;class has an&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">addressZip</code>&nbsp;property as well. The algorithm would match in the first split round already and essentially choose the wrong property and finally fail (as the type of&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">addressZip</code>&nbsp;probably has no&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">code</code>&nbsp;property).</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          To resolve this ambiguity you can use&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">_</code>&nbsp;inside your method name to manually define traversal points. So our method name would end up like so:</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
                          <pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">List</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Person</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findByAddress_ZipCode</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">ZipCode</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> zipCode</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span></code></pre>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          As we treat underscore as a reserved character we strongly advise to follow standard Java naming conventions (i.e.&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit; letter-spacing: -0.005em;">not</strong>using underscores in property names but camel case instead).</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="sect3" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                      <h4 id="repositories.special-parameters" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 300; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.4375em; word-spacing: -0.05em;">
                        4.4.4. Special parameter handling (파라미터로 Pageable 과 Sort 가 받아들여진다면, 이는 말하지 않아도pagenation 결과나 sorting 된 결과를 내라는 의미로 해석된다)</h4>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          To handle parameters in your query you simply define method parameters as already seen in the examples above. Besides that the infrastructure will recognize certain specific types like&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Pageable</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Sort</code>&nbsp;to apply pagination and sorting to your queries dynamically.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="exampleblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic;">
                          Example 14. Using Pageable, Slice and Sort in query methods</div>
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 1.25em; direction: ltr; border: 1px solid rgb(224, 224, 220); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: rgb(224, 224, 220) 0px 1px 4px; background: rgb(255, 254, 247);">
                          <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
											<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Page</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findByLastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> lastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Pageable</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> pageable</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Slice</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findByLastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> lastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Pageable</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> pageable</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">List</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findByLastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> lastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Sort</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> sort</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">List</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findByLastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> lastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Pageable</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> pageable</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span></code></pre>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          The first method allows you to pass an&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">org.springframework.data.domain.Pageable</code>&nbsp;instance to the query method to dynamically add paging to your statically defined query. A&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Page</code>&nbsp;knows about the total number of elements and pages available. It does so by the infrastructure triggering a count query to calculate the overall number. As this might be expensive depending on the store used,&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Slice</code>&nbsp;can be used as return instead. A&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Slice</code>&nbsp;only knows about whether there’s a next&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Slice</code>&nbsp;available which might be just sufficient when walking through a larger result set.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          Sorting options are handled through the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Pageable</code>&nbsp;instance too. If you only need sorting, simply add an<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">org.springframework.data.domain.Sort</code>&nbsp;parameter to your method. As you also can see, simply returning a&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">List</code>&nbsp;is possible as well. In this case the additional metadata required to build the actual&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Page</code>&nbsp;instance will not be created (which in turn means that the additional count query that would have been necessary not being issued) but rather simply restricts the query to look up only the given range of entities.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="admonitionblock note" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <table style="box-sizing: border-box; border-spacing: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25em; border: 0px; width: 970px; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">
                          <tbody style="box-sizing: border-box;">
                          <tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">
                            <td class="icon" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5625em 0.625em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6; text-align: center; width: 80px;">
                              &nbsp;</td>
                            <td class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5625em 1.25em 0.5625em 1.125em; direction: ltr; font-size: 1.0625rem; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em; border-left-style: solid; border-left-color: rgb(221, 221, 216);">
                              To find out how many pages you get for a query entirely you have to trigger an additional count query. By default this query will be derived from the query you actually trigger.</td>
                          </tr>
                          </tbody>
                        </table>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="sect3" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                      <h4 id="repositories.limit-query-result" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 300; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.4375em; word-spacing: -0.05em;">
                        4.4.5. Limiting query results - 메서드 이름속에 다양한 표현식으로 쿼리 결과를 변형, 제약하기</h4>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          The results of query methods can be limited via the keywords&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">first</code>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">top</code>, which can be used interchangeably. An optional numeric value can be appended to top/first to specify the maximum result size to be returned. If the number is left out, a result size of 1 is assumed.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="exampleblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic;">
                          Example 15. Limiting the result size of a query with&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; font-style: normal !important; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Top</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; font-style: normal !important; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">First</code></div>
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 1.25em; direction: ltr; border: 1px solid rgb(224, 224, 220); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: rgb(224, 224, 220) 0px 1px 4px; background: rgb(255, 254, 247);">
                          <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
											<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findFirstByOrder<span style="background-color:#ffff00;">ByLastnameAsc</span></span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findTopByOrder<span style="background-color:#ffff00;">ByAgeDesc</span></span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Page</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> query<span style="background-color:#ffff00;">First10</span>ByLastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> lastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Pageable</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> pageable</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Slice</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> find<span style="background-color:#ffff00;">Top3</span>ByLastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> lastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Pageable</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> pageable</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">List</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> find<span style="background-color:#ffff00;">First10</span>ByLastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> lastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Sort</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> sort</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">List</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findTop10ByLastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> lastname</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Pageable</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> pageable</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span></code></pre>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          The limiting expressions also support the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Distinct</code>&nbsp;keyword. Also, for the queries limiting the result set to one instance, wrapping the result into an&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Optional</code>&nbsp;is supported.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          If pagination or slicing is applied to a limiting query pagination (and the calculation of the number of pages available) then it is applied within the limited result.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="admonitionblock note" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <table style="box-sizing: border-box; border-spacing: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25em; border: 0px; width: 970px; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">
                          <tbody style="box-sizing: border-box;">
                          <tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">
                            <td class="icon" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5625em 0.625em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6; text-align: center; width: 80px;">
                              &nbsp;</td>
                            <td class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5625em 1.25em 0.5625em 1.125em; direction: ltr; font-size: 1.0625rem; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em; border-left-style: solid; border-left-color: rgb(221, 221, 216);">
                              Note that limiting the results in combination with dynamic sorting via a&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Sort</code>&nbsp;parameter allows to express query methods for the 'K' smallest as well as for the 'K' biggest elements.</td>
                          </tr>
                          </tbody>
                        </table>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="sect3" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                      <h4 id="repositories.query-streaming" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 300; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.4375em; word-spacing: -0.05em;">
                        4.4.6. 값을 Streaming 으로 비동기로 밀어낼 수 있는건가?? - Streaming query results</h4>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          The results of query methods can be processed incrementally by using a Java 8&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Stream&lt;T&gt;</code>&nbsp;as return type. Instead of simply wrapping the query results in a&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Stream</code>&nbsp;data store specific methods are used to perform the streaming.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="exampleblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic;">
                          Example 16. Stream the result of a query with Java 8&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; font-style: normal !important; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Stream&lt;T&gt;</code></div>
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 1.25em; direction: ltr; border: 1px solid rgb(224, 224, 220); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: rgb(224, 224, 220) 0px 1px 4px; background: rgb(255, 254, 247);">
                          <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
											<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="lit" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 102, 102);">@Query</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="str" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 136, 0);">"select u from User u"</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">)</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
