                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          This&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Person</code>&nbsp;has several attributes:</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="ulist" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <ul style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em 1.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; list-style-position: outside; font-family: inherit;">
                          <li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.625em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                              <code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">id</code>&nbsp;is the primary key</p>
                          </li>
                          <li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.625em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                              <code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">firstName</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">lastName</code>&nbsp;are data attributes</p>
                          </li>
                          <li style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.625em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                              <code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">address</code>&nbsp;is a link to another domain object</p>
                          </li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          Now assume we create a corresponding repository as follows:</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
									<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">interface</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">PersonRepository</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">extends</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">CrudRepository</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Person</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Long</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">{</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Person</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findPersonByFirstName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> firstName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">}</span></code></pre>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          Spring Data will return the domain object including all of its attributes. - 기본적으로는 모든 외래키에 연결된 객체의 전체 내용도 쿼리해서 로딩하게 된다. 그런데, Address 외래값의 디테일들을 전혀 원하지 않는다면?</p>
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          There are two options just to retrieve the<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">address</code>&nbsp;attribute. One option is to define a repository for&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Address</code>&nbsp;objects like this:</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
                          <pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">interface</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">AddressRepository</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">extends</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">CrudRepository</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Address</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Long</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">{}</span></code></pre>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          In this situation, using&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">PersonRepository</code>&nbsp;will still return the whole&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Person</code>&nbsp;object. Using&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">AddressRepository</code>&nbsp;will return just the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Address</code>.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          However, what if you do not want to expose&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">address</code>&nbsp;details at all? You can offer the consumer of your repository service an alternative by defining one or more projections.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="exampleblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic;">
                          Example 62. Simple Projection</div>
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 1.25em; direction: ltr; border: 1px solid rgb(224, 224, 220); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: rgb(224, 224, 220) 0px 1px 4px; background: rgb(255, 254, 247);">
                          <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
											<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">interface</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">NoAddresses</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">{</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">  </span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> getFirstName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> getLastName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">  </span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">}</span></code></pre>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                          <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                              This projection has the following details:</p>
                          </div>
                          <div class="colist arabic" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                            <table style="box-sizing: border-box; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; border: 0px; background: none;">
                              <tbody style="box-sizing: border-box;">
                              <tr style="box-sizing: border-box; background: none;">
                                <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.75em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1;">
                                  &nbsp;</td>
                                <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.25em 0px; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6;">
                                  A plain Java interface making it declarative.</td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr style="box-sizing: border-box; background: none;">
                                <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.75em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1;">
                                  &nbsp;</td>
                                <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.25em 0px; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6;">
                                  Export the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">firstName</code>.</td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr style="box-sizing: border-box; background: none;">
                                <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.75em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1;">
                                  &nbsp;</td>
                                <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.25em 0px; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6;">
                                  Export the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">lastName</code>.</td>
                              </tr>
                              </tbody>
                            </table>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          그냥, 리턴하는 객체를 선언하되, 동일한 프로퍼티명으로 된 선언들에게만 채워주게 된다.</p>
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          <span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.6;">The&nbsp;</span><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">NoAddresses</code><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;projection only has getters for&nbsp;</span><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">firstName</code><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">lastName</code><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;meaning that it will not serve up any address information. The query method definition returns in this case&nbsp;</span><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">NoAdresses</code><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.6;">&nbsp;instead of&nbsp;</span><code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">Person</code><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.6;">.</span></p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
									<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">interface</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">PersonRepository</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">extends</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">CrudRepository</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&lt;</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Person</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">,</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Long</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">&gt;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">{</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">NoAddresses</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> findByFirstName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> firstName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">);</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">}</span></code></pre>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                          Projections declare a contract between the underlying type and the method signatures related to the exposed properties. Hence it is required to name getter methods according to the property name of the underlying type. If the underlying property is named&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">firstName</code>, then the getter method must be named&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">getFirstName</code>&nbsp;otherwise Spring Data is not able to look up the source property. This type of projection is also called&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit;">closed projection</em>. Closed projections expose a subset of properties hence they can be used to optimize the query in a way to reduce the selected fields from the data store. The other type is, as you might imagine, an&nbsp;<em style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: inherit;">open projection</em>.</p>
                      </div>
                      <div class="sect4" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                        <h5 id="projections.remodelling-data" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 300; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.125em; word-spacing: -0.05em;">
                          Remodelling data - 아예 다형성된 도메인 클래스를 만들어서 다른 명칭의 프로퍼티로 매핑시킬 수 도 있다.</h5>
                        <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                            So far, you have seen how projections can be used to reduce the information that is presented to the user. Projections can be used to adjust the exposed data model. You can add virtual properties to your projection. Look at the following projection interface:</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="exampleblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic;">
                            Example 63. Renaming a property</div>
                          <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 1.25em; direction: ltr; border: 1px solid rgb(224, 224, 220); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: rgb(224, 224, 220) 0px 1px 4px; background: rgb(255, 254, 247);">
                            <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                              <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
												<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">interface</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">RenamedProperty</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">{</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">    </span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> getFirstName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">       </span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="lit" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 102, 102);">@Value</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="str" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 136, 0);">"#{target.lastName}"</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">) // &lt;--- 원래 도메인 클래스의 lastName 이 getName() 메서드로 접근가능하게끔 된 변형객체로 리턴된다.</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> getName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">            </span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">}</span></code></pre>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                              <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                                This projection has the following details:</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="colist arabic" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                              <table style="box-sizing: border-box; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; border: 0px; background: none;">
                                <tbody style="box-sizing: border-box;">
                                <tr style="box-sizing: border-box; background: none;">
                                  <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.75em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1;">
                                    &nbsp;</td>
                                  <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.25em 0px; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6;">
                                    A plain Java interface making it declarative.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr style="box-sizing: border-box; background: none;">
                                  <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.75em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1;">
                                    &nbsp;</td>
                                  <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.25em 0px; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6;">
                                    Export the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">firstName</code>.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr style="box-sizing: border-box; background: none;">
                                  <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0.75em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1;">
                                    &nbsp;</td>
                                  <td style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.25em 0px; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6;">
                                    Export the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">name</code>&nbsp;property. Since this property is virtual it requires&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">@Value("#{target.lastName}")</code>&nbsp;to specify the property source.</td>
                                </tr>
                                </tbody>
                              </table>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                            The backing domain model does not have this property so we need to tell Spring Data from where this property is obtained. Virtual properties are the place where&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">@Value</code>&nbsp;comes into play. The&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">name</code>&nbsp;getter is annotated with&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">@Value</code>&nbsp;to use&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/5.0.0.RC1/spring-framework-reference/html/expressions.html" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); line-height: inherit; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">SpEL expressions</a>&nbsp;pointing to the backing property&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">lastName</code>. You may have noticed&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">lastName</code>&nbsp;is prefixed with<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">target</code>&nbsp;which is the variable name pointing to the backing object. Using&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">@Value</code>&nbsp;on methods allows defining where and how the value is obtained.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                            Some applications require the full name of a person. Concatenating strings with&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">String.format("%s %s", person.getFirstName(), person.getLastName())</code>&nbsp;would be one possibility but this piece of code needs to be called in every place the full name is required. Virtual properties on projections leverage the need for repeating that code all over.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
										<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">interface</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">FullNameAndCountry</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">{</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="lit" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 102, 102);">@Value</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="str" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 136, 0);">"#{target.firstName} #{target.lastName}"</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">) // &lt;-- 이런식으로 값이 조합된 변형객체를 만들수도 있다. 기존 select .. as 를 대신해서 쓸 수 있다.</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> getFullName</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="lit" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 102, 102);">@Value</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="str" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 136, 0);">"#{target.address.country}"</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">)  // &lt;-- 특정 객체의 깊은 그래프 속의 값도 바깥으로 이끌어 낼 때도 사용.. 그냥 select 의 as 라고 보면 편하겠음.</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> getCountry</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">}</span></code></pre>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                            In fact,&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">@Value</code>&nbsp;gives full access to the target object and its nested properties. SpEL expressions are extremly powerful as the definition is always applied to the projection method. Let’s take SpEL expressions in projections to the next level.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                            Imagine you had the following domain model definition:</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
										<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="lit" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 102, 102);">@Entity</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
</span><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">public</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">class</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">User</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">{</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="lit" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 102, 102);">@Id</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="lit" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 102, 102);">@GeneratedValue</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
  </span><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">private</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">Long</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> id</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
  </span><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">private</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> name</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  </span><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">private</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> password</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">;</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
  </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">…</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">}</span></code></pre>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="admonitionblock important" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <table style="box-sizing: border-box; border-spacing: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.25em; border: 0px; width: 970px; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">
                            <tbody style="box-sizing: border-box;">
                            <tr style="box-sizing: border-box;">
                              <td class="icon" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5625em 0.625em; direction: ltr; font-size: inherit; line-height: 1.6; text-align: center; width: 80px;">
                                &nbsp;</td>
                              <td class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.5625em 1.25em 0.5625em 1.125em; direction: ltr; font-size: 1.0625rem; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em; border-left-style: solid; border-left-color: rgb(221, 221, 216);">
                                This example may seem a bit contrived, but it is possible with a richer domain model and many projections, to accidentally leak such details. Since Spring Data cannot discern the sensitivity of such data, it is up to the developers to avoid such situations. Storing a password as plain-text is discouraged. You really should not do this. For this example, you could also replace&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">password</code>&nbsp;with anything else that is secret.</td>
                            </tr>
                            </tbody>
                          </table>
                        </div>
                        <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                            In some cases, you might keep the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">password</code>&nbsp;as secret as possible and not expose it more than it should be. The solution is to create a projection using&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">@Value</code>&nbsp;together with a SpEL expression.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
										<pre class="prettyprint highlight prettyprinted" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.90625em; white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 1em; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; border-radius: 4px; word-wrap: break-word; border: 0px solid rgb(136, 136, 136); background: rgb(247, 247, 248);"><code class="language-java" data-lang="java" style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;"><span class="kwd" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 136);">interface</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">PasswordProjection</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> </span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">{</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
  </span><span class="lit" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 102, 102);">@Value</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">(</span><span class="str" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 136, 0);">"#{(target.password == null || target.password.empty) ? null : '******'}"</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">)  //--&gt; 함수를 넣을 수는 없을까? 그런데, 이게 JPQL 을 써서 as 를 넣고 싶다면, 어떻게 해야 하고, 뭐가 다른가???</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
  </span><span class="typ" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 0, 102);">String</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"> getPassword</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">();</span><span class="pln" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">
</span><span class="pun" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(102, 102, 0);">}</span></code></pre>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                            The expression checks whether the password is&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">null</code>&nbsp;or empty and returns&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">null</code>&nbsp;in this case, otherwise six asterisks to indicate a password was set.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="sect2" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                    <h3 id="jpa.stored-procedures" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px 0.5em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 300; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 1.6875em; word-spacing: -0.05em;">
                      5.4. Stored procedures</h3>
                    <div class="paragraph" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                      <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25rem; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">
                        The JPA 2.1 specification introduced support for calling stored procedures via the JPA criteria query API. We Introduced the&nbsp;<code style="box-sizing: border-box; font-family: &quot;Droid Sans Mono&quot;, &quot;DejaVu Sans Mono&quot;, monospace; font-size: 0.9375em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.901961); letter-spacing: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.5ex; word-spacing: -0.15em; border-radius: 4px; line-height: 1.45; text-rendering: optimizeSpeed; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 248);">@Procedure</code>&nbsp;annotation for declaring stored procedure metadata on a repository method.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="exampleblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                      <div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; line-height: 1.45; color: rgb(0, 136, 0); text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic;">
                        Example 64. The definition of the pus1inout procedure in HSQL DB.</div>
                      <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; padding: 1.25em; direction: ltr; border: 1px solid rgb(224, 224, 220); border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: rgb(224, 224, 220) 0px 1px 4px; background: rgb(255, 254, 247);">
                        <div class="listingblock" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr;">
                          <div class="content" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; direction: ltr; position: relative;">
